void MEEditNameDialog::setName (  int  nameIndex,
OldItem *  item,
OldGenericMap *  theMap
) 
 

Set the name that should be edited/added.

If the nameIndex is greater than the number of names for the given item, a new name could be added.

Parameters:
nameIndex The cardinal number of the name to edit. If more than the number of names for item, a new name is added.
item The item to edit/add name for.
theMap The map where the item and the names are located.

int MEEditNameDialog::m_nameOffset [protected]
 

The offset of the name in m_item.

Valid values if to change name are 0 <= m_nameOffset < m_item->getNbrNames(). If the value is outside this range, a new name will be added to m_item.
